    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA381-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai āṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaḷ paruva varaviṉkaṇ colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE who was unable to bear it in the time of separation said at the coming of the season.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA381">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            aruntuya ruḻattali ṉuṇmai cāṉmeṉap</l>
<l>            perumpiṟi tiṉmaiyi ṉilēṉu mallēṉ</l>
<l>            karaiporu tiḻitaruṅ kāṉyāṟ ṟikukarai</l>
<l>            vērkiḷar māat tantaḷir pōla</l>
<l>            naṭuṅka lāṉā neñcamō ṭiṭumpai</l>
<l>            yāṅkaṉan tāṅkuveṉ maṟṟē yōṅkucelaṟ</l>
<l>            kaṭumpakaṭ ṭiyāṉai neṭumā ṉañci</l>
<l>            yīra neñcamō ticaicēṇ viḷaṅkat</l>
<l>            tērvī cirukkai pōla</l>
<l>            māri yirīi māṉṟaṉṟāṉ maḻaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">            “Be up to a life of bearing difficult misery!” –<note place="foot">The <term xml:lang="ta">eṉa</term> at the end of this line might be interpreted to mean: even while I know there is a saying (= the general opinion is or the confidante say) of the following kind.</note></l>
<l>            I stand not for the not-being of the great other.<note place="foot">I.e. "I am not sure that I won’t die of it"; for <term xml:lang="ta">perum piṟitu</term> as a taboo expression for death cf. KT 69.1.</note></l>
<l>            How will I endure</l>
<l rend="indent">                the distress, with a heart shivering unendingly,</l>
<l rend="indent2">                as the pretty sprout of the mango tree the roots of which emerge</l>
<l rend="indent3">                on the breaking shore of the forest river that tumbles down hitting</l>
<l rend="indent4">                the shore?</l>
<l>            The rain has been profuse indeed, creating showers</l>
<l rend="indent">                as [liberal] as the chariot-giving court(?),</l>
<l rend="indent2">                while [his] fame shines widely, with an affected heart,</l>
<l rend="indent">                of Añci with big horses [and] loftily stepping fierce bull elephants.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
